Abdominal tergites brown and tergites 1–5 with sparse minute setulae only. Tergite VI (
Fig. 25C
) about triangular, each side with 2 long and 4–5 short setulae. Sternite VI (
Fig. 25D
) divided into two irregular pieces, each with 2 long and 2–3 short setulae. Oviscape arched. The dorsum of the oviscape with about 10 small setulae each side, three of those near apex are a little longer (
Fig.14F
).

Abdominal tergites brown, with sparse setulae at rear. Male terminalia brown and anal tube whitish yellow. Left side of epandrium with 5–6 long setulae (
Fig.15F
).
